description: When a giant-sized bat ransacks Gotham harbor, Batman suspects that Dr. Kirk Langstrom is up to his old tricks, taking the Man-Bat formula again. Batman isn't the only one. Kirk's wife, Francine, is so distrustful of her husband that she decides to leave him. After further investigation, Batman discovers that this Man-Bat is not Kirk, but someone else, and thus he shames Francine's father into permanently destroying the formula.
name: Terror in the Sky

description: Riddler is released from incarceration and sets to his shallow revenge to capture James Gordon into a virtual reality program as to entrap Batman into cyber-space with Robin aiding Batman in a true battle of the mind.
name: What Is Reality?
It Lives! It Grows! It Destroys!

deck: After a lab accident, police scientist Barry Allen is endowed with the powers of super speed.
description:
The series' pilot episode features an accident in which Central City Police forensic scientist Barry Allen's crime lab is struck by lightning. Allen's electrified body is flung into and shatters a cabinet of chemicals, which are both electrified and forced to interact with each other and with his physiology when they come into physical contact with his body. He soon discovers, with the help of S.T.A.R. Labs scientist Tina McGee, that the accident has changed his body's metabolism and as a result he has gained the ability to move at superhuman speed. To avenge the murder of his brother, motorcycle police officer Jay (Tim Thomerson), Barry demands that Tina modify a red S.T.A.R. Labs prototype deep sea diving suit, designed to withstand tremendous pressures, into his costume, to which she reluctantly complies. Thus, Barry Allen becomes the Flash.

*Jay Garrick appears as Jay Allen, Barry's older brother.
name: "Pilot"

description: Raid! An Assassin from Dressrosa! (襲来! ドレスローザからの刺客, Shūrai! Doresurōza kara no Shikaku)
name: Raid! An Assassin from Dressrosa!

description: An ex-bank-employee takes the bank hostage; when he agrees to release the bystanders he finds that his main victim, Lydecker, is replaced by Chance. After the attempted murder of Stephanie Dobbs the designer of a Californian bullet train, she hires Chance to protect her. He poses as her Japanese-English translator. Chance accompanies her on the train's first voyage – a three-hour trip from San Francisco to Los Angeles. When an attempted poisoning is spotted by Chance, the killer, dressed as a waiter, takes a more direct approach. Chance is able to fight him off and kill him. Meanwhile Guerrero and Winston discover that Dobbs used to have a relationship with reporter Mark Hoffer, to whom Dobbs anonymously leaked damaging information about the train manufacturer. Dobb's husband knew about the affair, but waited to kill her until she finished designing the train so that he could receive the financial bonus for its completion.
name: Pilot

deck: Spock leads a disastrous mission on the shuttle Galileo.
description: On Stardate 2821.5 Kirk sends Spock to lead a scientific team to study the quasar-like formation of four star systems.
name: The Galileo Seven

deck: The first episode.
description: The Serenity picks up a new group of passengers in order to make some extra money. But not all their passengers are as the seem.
name: Serenity
The City on the Edge of Forever

deck: When one of Sunnydale High's top swimmers is found dead and eviscerated, Buffy and friends start looking for a monster that eats humans but leaves the skin and cartilage behind.
description:
At a beach party Buffy and Xander catch the recently victorious Sunnydale High swim team tormenting nerdy student Jonathan. Buffy also makes a connection with one of the swimmers, Cameron.

On their first "date", however, Cameron tries to get frisky with Buffy who slams his head into the steering wheel of the car they're parked in. This is seen by Principal Snyder who takes blames Buffy. Snyder also tells Willow (who is still teaching the late Jenny Calendar's computer classes) to change another swimmer's grade to a "D", even though he just sits in class playing solitaire and doesn't even try.

One of the swimmers disappeared from the beach party and later his skin was found on the beach. And another one gets into a conflict with Xander just before Xander finds his lifeless skin seconds before a fish monster that attacks. And, when Angel tries to feed on yet another swimmer, he spits out the blood in disgust. All these things together lead Buffy, Giles, and the rest to deduce that the swim team is being turned into inhuman monsters.
name: Go Fish

deck: Leo lures the Manager of Dishwalla to P3, who has made a pack with demon that grants him fame and fortune in exchange for innocent souls. The charmed ones must stop this demon.
name: The Devil's Music

deck: Prue casts a spell that turns her into a man.
name: She's a Man, Baby, a Man !

deck: Sunnydale High is haunted by the ghost of a former student and teacher.
description:
Still reeling from her breakup with Angel, Buffy declines to go to the Sadie Hawkins dance with a boy who asks her to ask him.

On her way to the library she witnesses the attempted shooting of a girl by her boyfriend. But strangely there's no gun minutes after Buffy intervenes. Principal Snyder takes Buffy in for questioning.

The Scooby Gang soon learn that a murder/suicide that happened at Sunnydale High in the 1950s repeats itself every year on the eve of the Sadie Hawkins dance.
name: I Only Have Eyes for You

deck: Charmed ones must help a boy called Kyle to wield jeweled wand, to stop evil Witch.
name: That Old Black Magic

deck: Charmed ones must saved a patient and his son from demons.
name: They're Everywhere

deck: Whilst on political duties for the Republic, Yoda and his Clone Trooper escorts find themselves ambushed by the Separatists.
description: Great leaders inspire greatness in others.
name: Ambush

deck: The USS Enterprise visits a planet ruled by gangs like the mobs of 1920s Chicago
description:
The Enterprise visits a planet that was 'contaminated' by contact with a Federation starship in the days before the Prime Directive was put in place. A planet-wide cargo cult emulating 1920s Chicago developed. When they beam down, one of the mob bosses takes Kirk and Spock hostage, demanding weapons and training in exchange for their release.

While Oxmyx uses a communicator to negotiate the deal with Mr. Scott, Kirk manages to get the jump on the guards by distracting them with a made up card game before overturning the table at one while Spock delivers a Vulcan neck pinch to another.

Spock and Dr. McCoy use a radio transmitter to contact Uhura to beam up, but Kirk is captured by Krako, a rival boss. Krako (who has a dartboard of 'OKMYX' in his office) offers to cut Kirk in on the action if he gives him the weapons instead of Oxmyx. When Kirk refuses, Krako has him locked up.

Oxmyx again contacts The Enterprise to let them know Kirk has fallen into Krako's hands. He offers to help rescue Kirk for an unspecified reward. Though they don't trust him, Spock and McCoy accept; he of course double crosses them and takes them prisoner. However, Kirk effects an escape from Krako and shows up to turn the tables on Oxmyx.

Dressing up like gangsters, Kirk and Spock attempt to take over Krako's base with the help of a boy who offers help for 'a piece of the action'. Once in Krako's office, Kirk informs Krako that the Federation is taking over the whole planet, but offers him a "piece of the action" to be their puppet underboss. Krako agrees and Kirk has Scotty beam him aboard the Enterprise. They contact Oxmyx and offer the same deal. Krako is transported back to the planet and all the bosses are called together for a meeting at Oxmyx's headquarters. Kirk informs them the Feds are taking over, but the planet needs to be run like a business. The Federation will come once a year to collect 40% of the profits with Oxmyx left in charge and Krako as his second in command.

They return to the ship and leave Sigma Iotia II. When Spock questions the Federation's 40% cut, Kirk says the funds will be used to help shepherd Iotian society toward civility. Unfortunately McCoy reveals that they have further contaminated the planet as he left his communicator behind. Kirk muses that the Iotians will no doubt reverse engineer it, and they might one day come back demanding a piece of the action from the Federation.
name: A Piece of the Action

deck: Three ancient beings, the last of their race require the bodies of Captain Kirk, Mr. Spock, and Dr. Mulhall.
description:
Following the events of 'By Any Other Name', The Enterprise is at one of the farthest reaches of the galaxy when it comes across an M class planet that has been devastated by cataclysm. A disembodied voice, identifying itself only as 'Sargon', claims that it has summoned the ship there, and instructs Captain Kirk to beam a party down to a cave miles beneath the surface.

When the party arrives, however, they learn that Sargon wishes to take over the body of James Kirk, and install two others of his race in the bodies of Officer Spock and Dr. Mulhall.
name: Return to Tomorrow

deck: In search of a missing Federation historian, The USS Enterprise comes across a planet with a global government resembling Nazi Germany.
description:
The Enterprise travels to the planet Ekos where Federation historian John Gill has gone missing. Upon approach their ship is targeted by a nuclear missile, technology far above what the primitive, anarchic peoples were believed to be capable of.

Captain Kirk and Science Officer Spock beam down to investigate. What they find is a planet reminiscent of Nazi Germany. The pair are soon captured and imprisoned. There they learn from another prisoner that Ekon society had been transmuted from a primitive society to a Nazi dictatorship in just a few short years - coinciding with John Gill's arrival there.

Effecting an escape from the prison Kirk, Spock and the other prisoner join an underground resistance movement. They know that the only way they can solve this mess is to speak to The Führer himself, John Gill.
name: Patterns of Force

deck: The 11th episode of High School DXD.
name: The Acclaimed Battle Continues!

deck: The 12th episode of High School DXD.
name: I'm Here to Keep My Promise!

deck: High School DXD 1st Season OVA (One).
name: I'm Harvesting Breasts!

deck: High School DXD 1st Season OVA (Two).
name: I'm Searching for Breasts!

deck: High School DXD: New's 1st Episode.
name: Another Disquieting Premonition!

deck: High School DXD: New's 2nd Episode.
name: The Holy Sword Is Here!

deck: High School DXD: New's 3rd Episode.
name: I'll Destroy the Holy Sword!

description:
Intro:

Batman and Mr. Miracle are in a death trap!

Rest of the episode:

Batman takes a trip to the future, where he meets Kamandi. The two fight against anthropomorphis creatures ( were-bats, for example). Then, after the villains have been defeated, he returns to his own era.
name: The Last Bat on Earth

series.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
Intro:

Batman, Hawk & Dove are in space, aiming to stop two warring alien races!

Rest of the episode:

Global peace agency wants Batman to help one of their agents on a mission. Buddy Blank, who can be turned to OMAC, a juggernaut of justice! He`s pretty arrogant. Buddy is flimsy, and not arrogant at all. He has no idea of his changes.

To this mission they go. The mission being, to snuff out the threat of a mad marshal man named Kafka, who wants to nuke a country.

The two heroes fight against his forces, and Omac blows up the factory where they are. The mad despot doesn`t get out alive. Oh wait, he does. And now he has superpowers! He names himself Shrapnel.

He wants to destroy a nuclear reactor, which will increase his power (because he absorbs energy). And destroy a city.

OMAC barges to Shrapnels way, and beats him up. Shrapnel becomes stronger due to the kinetic energy of OMACs punches.

Batman tries to stop Shrapnel, but is stopped himself. By a cosmic being called Equinox. He explains that Shrapnel needs to destroy the reactor, so that the city would die. Why?

Cosmic balance. Shrapnel wanted to destroy a city earlier. Since he was stopped then, he mustn`t be, this time. Batman doesn`t agree.

Shrapnel is in the nuclear factory, and radiation levels are growing dangerously high. Batman tries to stop him. Loses.

Then OMAC realizes that Shrapnel can be defeated if he doesn`t fight against him. This OMAC does, wins, and reverts back to Buddy, because there`s a time limit for the transformation.

Buddy, who has been treated as a pushover for years, decides to something heroic, and beat the superpowered menace of Equinox. He loses too.

But before he does, Batman sneaks to the reactor (where radiation levels are so high that they will surely kill), to stop it from blowing up.

He nearly dies, but is revived by Equinox for the sake of balance. Then Equinox skidaddles.

Batman and Buddy (feeling courageous) just, you know, hang out for a while, before the end credits blast to the screen.

Written by Stan Berkowitz.
name: When Omac Attacks!

series.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
Intro:

Green Arrow and Batman face Catwoman! Don`t miss the flirting between Batsy and Catsy!

Rest of the episode:

It`s time for Batman and the Outsiders again! This time, the team of rookie heroes have been captured by Psycho pirate, who has attached them to a machine which makes them go trough their worst fears! It`s up to Batman to help them defeat them!
name: Inside The Outsiders!

series.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
In this musical episode, heroes and villains dance and sing to the tune of the mighty Music meister! There`s alot of chameos, romantic tension (between Green arrow, Black canary and Batman) and precisely coreographed action in store! AND singing!

Written by Michael Jelenic.

Season one finale.
name: Mayhem of the Music Meister!

series.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

deck: With Batman gone and Gotham vulnerable, Barbara Gordon forms a team to protect her city. Recruiting the secret daughter of Batman and a runaway teen, they form the Birds of Prey.
description: A duo of female crime fighters, protégés of Batman, gets a new member while investigating a strange series of deaths caused by fear. This unaired pilot was reedited and the role of Dr. Harleen Quinzel recast to create the new pilot.
name: Pilot

deck: Dr. Quinzel has hired a dangerous meta-human named Slick to take out those that stand in her way.
name: Slick

deck: Helena tracks a serial killer who is murdering meta-humans by stealing their powers.
name: Prey for the Hunter

deck: When an abandoned baby is brought to the Clocktower, Helena is put in grave danger.
name: Three Birds and a Baby

deck: Barbara and Helena discover the truth behind Dinah, while Dinah learns about her hidden past.
name: Sins of the Mother

description:
Intro:

Batman vs. Two-face!

Rest of the episode:

Equinox (whose origin is told) wants to remake the universe to be the way he wants, and only a handful of heroes can stop him!

End of season one.

Written by Joseph Kuhr.
name: The Fate of Equinox!

series.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

deck: Helena goes undercover in an attempt to take down a gang terrorising the streets of Gotham.
name: Primal Scream

deck: An intriguing new meta-human comes to town, but Barbara and Dinah discover his dangerous alter-ego.
name: Split

deck: Barbara suspects Lady Shiva is back in Gotham, and begins experimenting with technology that may allow her to get out of her wheelchair.
name: Lady Shiva

deck: Helena's loyalties are tested when she is tasked with protecting the mob boss who killed Dinah's mother.
name: Nature of the Beast

description: Obsessed with his feelings for Sara Pezzini and driven by the spirt of Kenneth Irons, Ian Nottingham contracts with a group of deadly assassins, The Black Dragons, to murder Sara.
name: Consectatio

deck: Women are being kidnapped and forced to fight each other in underground arenas. After Helena is abducted too, it is up to Dinah to come to her rescue.
name: Gladiatrix

deck: With her High School reunion looming, Helena discovers that her old classmates are turning up dead.
name: Reunion

deck: Helena pays a visit to Arkham Asylum to interrogate Clayface about a new meta-human who possesses his powers.
name: Feat of Clay

deck: Harley Quinn gives herself meta-human powers after discovering that Helena is Huntress.
name: Devil's Eyes

deck: Kirk, Spock, and McCoy investigate a planet where the crew of the USS Exeter last visited before leaving their craft in unmanned orbit around the planet.
description:
The USS Exeter is discovered still orbiting the planet it last communicated from six months prior. A boarding party discovers the crew have all succumbed to a strange ailment. Believing they will infect the Enterprise if they return they go down to the planets surface where they soon become embroiled in an ancient tribal conflict.

Captain Ron Tracey, the Exeter's Captain is found to be leading one of the two factions, in violation of the Prime Directive. When Kirk refuses to go along with his plan he has Kirk and Spock locked up and forces McCoy to do medical research to discover the secret to the native population's natural longevity.
name: The Omega Glory

deck: The Sarcophagus of Acathla is unearthed. Acathla is a demon that was turned to stone who, if revived, will suck everyone on Earth into Hell. Angel intends to do just that.
description:
Angel steals the Sarcophagus of Acathla from a museum, intending to bring Acathla back to life.

Buffy and Willow discover the disc with Jenny Calendar's notes on how to re-curse Angel. This leads to a very heated debate among the Scooby Gang.

Kendra arrives with an ominous message from her watcher that something terrible is going to happen.
name: Becoming Part 1

deck: Angelus tortures Giles to learn how to awaken Acathla. Whistler tells Buffy that Angel's blood is the key both to opening and closing the portal to Hell.
description: The police try to apprehend Buffy, but Spike comes to her rescue and offers a temporary alliance. He doesn't want the world to be destroyed, and wants Drusilla back. He agrees to help Buffy stop Angelus if she lets him and Drusilla leave the country. Buffy reluctantly agrees.
name: Becoming: Part 2

deck: Buffy has created a new life for herself in another city; but her old life won't stay buried for long.
description: Using her middle name, Anne, Buffy works as a diner waitress in a big city. One of her customers, Lily, recognizes her from the episode "Lie To Me" when Lily was known as "Chanterelle". When Lily's boyfriend Ricky disappears, she begs Buffy for help.
name: Anne

deck: When Joyce Summers' Nigerian mask reanimates the dead, Buffy has to fight a horde of zombies.
description:
Buffy's mom hangs a Nigerian mask given to her by a gallery friend in her bedroom. Buffy avoids most questions about her summer from friends and family, and Giles similarly seems to want to keep a stiff upper lip and avoid the topic. Principal Snyder meanwhile, remains adamant about keeping Buffy out of Sunnydale High.

When Buffy finds a dead cat in the basement and buries it in the garden, and it shows back up the next day, she calls Giles, knowing something is about to get very weird.
name: Dead Man's Party

deck: The Enterprise is chosen to participate in Starfleet wargames to test The Ultimate Computer
description:
Dr. Daystrom, creator of the computer technology that drives all Federation ships has perfected his latest 'multitronic' computer, the M5, which will replace the older duotronic devices in current Starfleet ships.

On orders from Starfleet, the USS Enterprise is outfitted with the M5 and only a skeleton crew, and ordered to participate in wargames against a small attack force to test the M5's capabilities.

The M5, however, is an artificial intelligence, and it immediately acts in the interest of self-preservation by locking all controls and using deadly force against all perceived hostilities.
name: The Ultimate Computer

deck: Sent back in time to observe a critical moment in Earth's history, The Enterprise stumbles across a man armed with alien technology who intends to alter the course of human history, but are his intentions for good or ill?
description: The Enterprise is sent back in time to 1968 to observe Earth's history at a critical moment. Upon arrival they accidentally intercept a transporter transmission from a great distance, beaming a man who says his name is "Gary Seven", and a black cat he calls "Isis", aboard the ship. Seven claims that he has been sent by an advanced alien race to prevent World War III, but Captain Kirk doesn't trust him and has him detained until he can figure out who he really is.
name: Assignment: Earth

deck: In Central City, homeless people are disappearing but nobody can find their bodies.
name: Out of Control

deck: A corrupt DA blackmails Barry, otherwise he will expose his secret.
name: Watching the Detectives

deck: A group of thieves attempt to steal a valuable object donated to Central City Museum.
name: Honor Among Theives
